			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well I read all the past comments about mage pets, some I agree with and some I disagree with.  Heres my views -<BR>
<BR>
When soloing I use a LOT more mana if using an earth pet and it also gets hurt bad.<BR>
<BR>
The most mana efficient I have found so far is <BR>
1) cast 1 nuke to pull mob<BR>
2) set pet to attack<BR>
3) after a few seconds cast another 2 nukes<BR>
4) Mob will agro you (you should be anticipating this) so start walking backwards (you did maintain a safe distance from the beginning i hope)<BR>
5) Mob will either get 1 hit on you before pet kills it, or will die as it comes to hit you.<BR>
<BR>
Pet is left with 80%+ HP, your left with about 90% mana, and you get hit twice max.<BR>
<BR>
Air pet - great against casters.<BR>
<BR>
Ok something I don't understand here... somebody said fire pets aren't good in groups because of low HP, and the damage shield is useless because they can't taunt off a warrior... Well, if your pet isnt going to get hit then HP is instantly out of the equasion, so hardest hitter must be your priority.<BR>
<BR>
Water pet - decent all rounder.<BR>
<BR>
I thought an earth pet with damage shield (getting hit all the time) would be more mana and killing effective, but this definately isn't the case.<BR>
<BR>
Also, if I set a pet to attack, and then heal the pet without casting any nukes, I generally lose the pet just before the mob dies which means I have to melee the mob to death.  Note this isn't as easy as it always seems - me with full health versus a blue con mob with maybe 20HP left, I still died.  Meleeing at higher levels us practically impossible for magicians, and completly foolish heh.<BR>
<BR>
Lallaar &lt;Tarot&gt; of Prexus
				</font>
			</td>

